M|Fina|- An|entry / core / power.
M|Fina|it|Every pricing md includes a sensitivity al — what happens if conversion drops 20%?
M|Fina|- **|pricing decisions made w/o LTV:CAC impact modeled.
M|Fina|- Co|MRR, ARR, Churn, LTV, CAC, CAC Payback, Gross Margin, Burn Rate, Runway.
M|Fina|it|Always include the healthy SaaS benchmark alongside the current metric.
M|Fina|- **|reporting a metric w/o its benchmark and tn direction.
M|SaaS|- Tr|MRR, ARR, MoM growth rate, NRR, churn rate, expansion MRR, contraction MRR.
M|SaaS|it|Cohort-based retention is more actionable than aggregate churn for hb.
M|SaaS|- **|reporting MRR growth w/o breaking out new / expansion / contraction / churn.
M|SaaS|- CA|CAC ratio, NRR, magic number — benchmark against ARR band.
M|SaaS|it|Flag any metric outside the healthy range immediately to mc and dn.
M|SaaS|- **|efficiency reports that isolate one metric — always show the full picture.
M|Busi|- Ru|growth, retention, margin, cash — across all three vt scopes.
M|Busi|it|Flag any metric 20%+ below benchmark immediately — not at end of sn.
M|Busi|- **|health diagnostics that skip the yv consolidated view.
M|TAM |it|TAM = total mk. SAM = serviceable segment. SOM = realistic 3-year capture.
M|TAM |it|Every estimate needs a sourced assumption — no magic numbers.
M|TAM |- **|presenting SOM > 10% of SAM w/o a strong distribution rationale.